## How to Choose: The Orient Effect in Practice

The framework is simple. Answer one question first: **Does this pendant need to elongate or anchor?**

Point-up pendants elongate. The teardrop drop pulls the eye downward along the neckline, creating a vertical line that makes necklines look longer. This is why point-up pear pendants dominated the red carpet in 2023–2025 and why they pair best with V-neck and open necklines. The same elongating logic applies to rings — see the [pear shaped diamond ring settings guide](/pear-shaped-diamond-ring) for how orientation affects finger length.

East-west pendants anchor. The horizontal line fills the collarbone laterally, reading like a bar necklace with curves. It pairs best with boat necks, round necks, and high necklines. The [EW Bezel 0.25 CTW at $1,220](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/east-west-bezel-solitaire-pendant-necklace-with-025-ctw-pear-shaped-diamond-in-14k-white-gold-item-297496?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) wears very differently than a [Point Up 1/4 ct at $600](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/point-up-pear-cut-lab-grown-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-yellow-gold-1-4-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251318?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) even though the stone weight is nearly identical.

Tennis necklaces sit above this decision — they don't drop, they encircle. The [7 CTW Tennis in 14K White Gold at $12,640](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/east-west-bezel-tennis-necklace-with-7-ctw-pear-shaped-diamonds-in-14k-white-gold-item-297456?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is not a pendant at all — it is a statement band that replaces the neckline entirely.

---

## Lab vs Natural for Pear Pendants

For pendant solitaires, lab vs natural is a genuine decision with meaningful trade-offs. A [Point Up Pear Lab 1 ct at $930](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/point-up-pear-cut-lab-grown-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-yellow-gold-1-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251324?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is F-G/VS2-SI1. The natural 1/2 ct H-I/SI1-SI2 at [Point Up Natural 1/2 ct at $2,370](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/point-up-pear-cut-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-yellow-gold-1-2-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251319?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is half the size at 2.5x the cost. That is the lab premium in plain numbers.

Natural makes sense in two cases: investment (pendants worn and passed down hold resale value, lab does not), or provenance preference. The [JA Bezel Natural 1 ct Platinum at $5,859](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/bezel-solitaire-pendant-necklace-with-1-ctw-pear-shaped-diamond-in-platinum-by-james-allen-item-310944?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is a piece that will appreciate. The [Point Up Lab 3 ct at $2,292](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/point-up-pear-cut-lab-grown-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-yellow-gold-3-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251327?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) will not — but you will be wearing 3 carats around your neck for $2,292. For the same stone in a ring, see our [pear diamond engagement ring guide](/pear-diamond-engagement-ring) for setting comparisons.

For tennis necklaces, the calculus shifts. Individual stones in a tennis necklace carry no provenance premium, cannot be identified individually, and are never resold as components. Lab tennis is the rational default unless you specifically want natural for documentation purposes.

---

> **Farzana's Take:** "The pear pendant is the most misunderstood necklace in jewelry. People buy the smallest stone they can afford when they should be buying the biggest lab stone available — because the neck is the one context where face-up size always wins. I have never once heard someone say their pear pendant was too large. The [3 ct lab in yellow gold at $2,292](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/point-up-pear-cut-lab-grown-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-yellow-gold-3-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251327?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) changes the way a room looks at you. That is not hyperbole."

